{"source_key":"sha256-67ab078c7f660fb9364b7c83113ccb67","record_index":775,"record_hash":"sha256:010b50306396eb256b7e917d0d511643bf9a34eb78d95f1151764bed97099067","timestamp":"2026-06-04T15:58:42.863Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes. `query:error` is just the envelope. It has useful fields:\n\n`command`, `error_title`, `error_code`, `error_message`, plus repo/session/user context.\n\nCurrent biggest `0.20.0` `query:error` classes:\n\n| Class | Events | Users | Share |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| `list_reviews`: GitHub 403 listing PRs | 512 | 45 | 19.6% |\n| `forge_provider`: `Target ref required for remote url` | 192 | 73 | 7.4% |\n| no command: `pulls/get` load failed `api.github.com` | 165 | 21 | 6.3% |\n| `list_reviews`: GitHub 404 listing PRs | 151 | 13 | 5.8% |\n| no command: `users/getAuthenticated` requires auth | 118 | 28 | 4.5% |\n| no command: `checks/listForRef` load failed | 96 | 24 | 3.7% |\n| `head_info`: workspace commit guard | 55 | 9 | 2.1% |\n| `is_gerrit`: credential prompt failure | 49 | 8 | 1.9% |\n\nThe biggest observability gap: lots of rows have **no `command`**. Those are mostly GitHub/GitLab client errors, not Tauri command errors:\n\n- `pulls/get`\n- `checks/listForRef`\n- `users/getAuthenticated`\n- GitLab `TypeError: Load failed`\n- rate limits\n- missing commits/refs\n\nSo yes, we can break it down, but we should probably improve instrumentation: add a `command`/`operation` equivalent for forge API calls, or at least `provider`, `api_method`, `host`, and sanitized status/code. Right now `query:error` mixes backend commands and frontend forge calls, which makes the top-level bucket look mushy.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-06-04T15:58:42.863Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}